President Trump expressed support for his former Labor Secretary, Alex Acosta, amid his resignation following criticism of his handling of a plea deal for financier Jeffrey Epstein. Trump praised Acosta's job performance and said that he did not need to resign. Acosta explained that he made the decision to step down in order to shift the focus back to the administration's accomplishments, particularly the strong economy. Trump also discussed his views on immigration, the upcoming Robert Mueller testimony, and his thoughts on the infighting among Democrats in Congress. He also addressed the issue of ICE raids and the condition of detention centers, stating that Vice President Pence and the head of Homeland Security would be touring the facilities. Trump mentioned his ongoing efforts to build a border wall and his recent legal victory in the emoluments case. He warned Iran to be cautious, stating that they are treading on dangerous territory.